body:
Compiling recent Verilator versions (5.006, 4.228) with gcc-6.4.0 yields a handful of errors like this:
```
In file included from ../V3Assert.h:23:0,
                 from ../Verilator.cpp:19:
../V3Ast.h:2375:33: error: specialization of ‘template<class _Tp> struct std::hash’ in different namespace [-fpermissive]
 struct std::hash<VNRef<T_Node>> final {
                                 ^~~~~
In file included from /tools/gnu/gcc-6.4.0/include/c++/6.4.0/bits/basic_string.h:5643:0,
                 from /tools/gnu/gcc-6.4.0/include/c++/6.4.0/string:52,
                 from /tools/gnu/gcc-6.4.0/include/c++/6.4.0/bits/locale_classes.h:40,
                 from /tools/gnu/gcc-6.4.0/include/c++/6.4.0/bits/ios_base.h:41,
                 from /tools/gnu/gcc-6.4.0/include/c++/6.4.0/ios:42,
                 from /tools/gnu/gcc-6.4.0/include/c++/6.4.0/ostream:38,
                 from /tools/gnu/gcc-6.4.0/include/c++/6.4.0/iostream:39,
                 from ../config_build.h:65,
                 from ../V3Active.h:20,
                 from ../Verilator.cpp:17:
/tools/gnu/gcc-6.4.0/include/c++/6.4.0/bits/functional_hash.h:58:12: error:   from definition of ‘template<class _Tp> struct std::hash’ [-fpermissive]
     struct hash;
            ^~~~
...
```
